ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC STDIZE <options> ; 
      BY variables ; 
      FREQ variable ; 
      LOCATION variables ; 
      SCALE variables ; 
      VAR variables ; 
      WEIGHT variable ; 

The STDIZE procedure standardizes one or more numeric variables in a SAS data set by subtracting a 
location measure and dividing by a scale measure.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: VAR variable ; 

The VAR statement lists numeric variables to be standardized. If you omit the VAR statement, all 
numeric variables not listed in the BY, FREQ, and WEIGHT statements are used.

Syntax: WEIGHT variable;

The WEIGHT statement specifies a numeric variable in the input data set with values that are used 
to weight each observation. Only one variable can be specified.

Syntax: LOCATION variables ;

The LOCATION statement specifies a list of numeric variables that contain location measures
in the input data set specified by the METHOD=IN option.

Syntax: SCALE variables ; 

The SCALE statement specifies the list of numeric variables containing scale measures in the input 
data set specified by the METHOD=IN option.
